      "message": "Note that SkWGL_win.cpp already has platform #ifdef around its contents. It would probably be better to add \" \u0026\u0026 !defined(WINUWP)\" there so that the platform tests are all in one place instead of split between this build file and the source file.\n\nIt shouldn\u0027t be needed to remove SkWGL.h from sources since it won\u0027t get built by itself (if it ever is then it will need similar though maybe slightly different #ifdef as SkWGL_win.cpp).\n\nNote that this isn\u0027t the greatest solution and I would prefer whether or not the content of a file is built to be determined by the build files and not in preprocessor macros. However, splitting this half and half between the source file and the build file seems worse than having it in one place or the other.",
